roadband subscriptions.\n*   **Enterprise & Government:** Business broadband, government/defense communications solutions, and **Starlink Mobile** service offerings (aimed at reducing global mobile "dead zones").\n\n**AI Business Lines:**\n*   **Advertising:** Revenue generated via the X platform.\n*   **AI Solutions & Infrastructure:** Enterprise and consumer AI offerings, including *Grok Business* and *Grok Enterprise*, which are sold on license-, consumption-, or outcome-based pricing models.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Major Initiatives and Growth Strategies\nThe company outlines several ambitious, large-scale initiatives and growth strategies driven by its mission to "make life multiplanetary, understand the true nature of the universe, and extend the light of consciousness to the stars":\n\n**Infrastructure & Technology Scaling:**\n*   **Starship Development:** Heavily investing in the next-generation *Starship* launch platform to drastically increase launch cadence and lower the cost of space access.\n*   **Orbital AI Compute & Chip Manufacturing:** Initiatives to develop "orbital AI compute at scale" and "manufacture AI chips at scale" to support its AI segment\'s infrastructure needs.\n*   **Starlink Mobile Expansion:** Expanding the Starlink Mobile offering to provide continuous global coverage and eliminate structural mobile "dead zones" left by traditional terrestrial network operators.\n\n**Monetization & Market Penetration:**\n*   **Near-Term Revenue Focus:** Focused on increasing the monetization of its existing Connectivity infrastructure (growing the subscriber base and enterprise/government sales) and its existing AI user base.\n*   **Government & Defense Solutions:** Capitalizing on the $5B+ global satellite communications market driven by defense and government demand for resilient, secure, and low-latency communications in contested/remote environments.\n\n**Frontier & Deep Space Initiatives:**\n*   **Lunar & Martian Exploration:** Initiatives to establish