erate the pace of these investments at any time to maintain reliability and competitiveness.\n*   To fund these future growth investments and maintain strong liquidity, the company plans to access a range of **debt and equity financing solutions** available to it as a public company.\n\n**Space Segment Commitments:**\n*   Significant additional capital resources will be required for the continued **development, testing, and deployment of Starship**.\n*   Future CapEx will also support the pursuit of orbital AI, other space-related services, and lunar and interplanetary missions.\n\n**AI Segment Commitments:**\n*   The company expects a **multi-year investment horizon** before AI infrastructure deployments translate into sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n*   Substantial ongoing CapEx will be dedicated to obtaining third-party GPUs, manufacturing proprietary GPUs, and constructing, leasing, maintaining, and expanding data centers.\n*   During this investment period, AI capital expenditures will **"scale as quickly as we are able to deploy power and compute"** to capture a projected $26.5 trillion potential market opportunity for AI.',
